Genesis overall was pretty solid. Like any experience there were a few snafus (though not related to the event directly, having no service in the middle of a major city is quite frustrating), but it was overall a really well run tournament with tons of great matches.

Not sure how much traveling I'll be doing in the near future, not a huge fan of flying and vacation days are sparse. But I'll see what comes up - Smash is too sick to just experience it all from home.

As a final note, the number of times I saw someone with EchoStats on their Twitter feed was mindboggling. It's hard to understand just through the analytics, but seeing it in person really made me realize just how many people are following. Thank you all for the support.
